Q:
A great many countries around the world are losing their cultural identity because of the
Internet.
To what extent do you agree or disagree with this statement?

A:

Internet is just another information distribution channel, like TV, magazines and others
Internet in on-demand information source
Internet is well spreaded only in developed countries (and even there there are regions with out good coverage)

1.  What is cultural identity? Holidays, clothes, language, habbits.

2.  Only social networks join people with different cultures, but such resources cannot make big impact because of the type of the content placed there.


First of all, lets difine the meaning of the words "cultural identity". Speaking about the differences in cultures and nationalities we often come to such things as clothes, habbits, music, art, food and of course language. For instance, here in Russia ..
